<H3> <TI>   Chief Cabinet Secretary on Monetary Intervention </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chief Cabinet Secretary on Monetary Intervention </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2606195494 Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN in Japanese 24 Jun 
94 Evening Edition p 3 -- FOR OFFICIAL USE ONLY </F>

<F P=103> OW2606195494 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo NIHON KEIZAI SHIMBUN </F>
<F P=105>  Japanese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] At a news conference after a 24 June cabinet 
meeting, Chief Cabinet Secretary Hiroshi Kumagai commented on 
the yen's rebound on New York Foreign Exchange Market, saying: 
"Finance Minister Hirohisa Fujii has also repeatedly said the 
government will deal with currency movements with a resolute 
attitude. We will maintain this attitude while considering a 
concerted intervention with other countries." He thus indicated 
a strong possibility of a concerted dollar-buying intervention 
in currency markets with the United States and European 
countries. 

</TEXT>

