<F P=100> South Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Reportage on Strike Developments Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reportage on Strike Developments Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    ONR To Dismiss Striking Engineers </H4>

<F P=102> SK2706013994 Seoul CHOSON ILBO in Korean 27 Jun 94 p 1 </F>
<F P=103> SK2706013994 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul CHOSON ILBO </F>
<F P=105>  Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> [By reporter Kwon Sang-un] </F>
  [Text] On 26 June, the Office of National Railroads [ONR] 
disclosed its plan to mete out strong disciplinary measures-- 
including the deprivation of their status or dismissal from 
their posts--on the members of the National Council of 
Locomotive Engineers [NCLE] who have not yet reported to their 
work after the deadline set for their return has passed, by 
classifying them into several categories, depending on the 
degree of their active participation in the strike. The ONR has 
also decided to dismiss some 500 employees, including about 210 
who have not yet returned to work after they were released by 
the police with a warning, and the executives of the NCLE 
headquarters and its 20 nation-wide branch offices. 

</TEXT>

