<H3> <TI>   Official Visits Moscow, Discusses Security Issue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Official Visits Moscow, Discusses Security Issue </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2406080394 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1622 GMT 23 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2406080394 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, June 23. (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The 
secretary of the National Security Council of Mongolia J. 
Enhsaihan was on an official visit to the Russian Federation in 
June 19-23 at the invitation of his Russian colleague O.I. 
Lobov. During meetings and talks they have exchanged views on 
many aspects of Mongolian-Russian mutual relations. In view of 
J. Enhsaihan and O.I. Lobov priority importance in the 
Mongolian-Russian mutual relations should be attached to the 
issues of regional and international security, strengthening 
nuclear free status of Mongolia, economic security, struggle 
with criminality, international terrorism, illegal transit 
transportation of arms, narcotics. 
  In the near future a visit of the secretary of the National 
Security Council of the Russian Federation to Mongolia is 
expected, as a result of which a document on cooperation in the 
national security sphere will be signed, informs today the press 
service of the Ministry for External Relations of Mongolia. 

</TEXT>

