<H3> <TI>   `Revived' NOVOSTI MONGOLII Published </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    `Revived' NOVOSTI MONGOLII Published </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2806013694 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1701 GMT 27 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2806013694 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, June 27 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- The first 
issue of the revived newspaper "NOVOSTI MONGOLII" has appeared. 
The newspaper started appearing in Russian language from 1942, 
but in January in 1991 it was closed because of financial 
difficulties, well-known complications in the Mongolian-Soviet 
relations. 
  Today "NOVOSTI MONGOLII" is revived rather as an economic 
commercial newspaper. In the new issue the majority of 
materials is devoted to problems of Mongolian-Russian economic 
relations. The newspaper publishes the interviews of the 
vice-premier C. Purebdorj, the ambassador of the Russian 
Federation to Mongolia S.S. Razov, an article by the well-known 
scientist-economist, Dr. P. Nergui devoted to Mongolian economy 
of the present day and tendencies for her development. 
  The newspaper also publishes materials about cultural life 
and information for foreign tourists. 
  On the occasion of the first issue of "NOVOSTI MONGOLII" the 
ceremony of presentation was held today at the House of Russian 
Science and Culture. 

</TEXT>

