<H3> <TI>   Japan Offers Credits To Finance Hanoi Airport </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Japan Offers Credits To Finance Hanoi Airport </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2806093494 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam in English 1000 GMT 27 
Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2806093494 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Japan has decided to offer Vietnam official credits 
to help finance the construction of a new international airport 
in Hanoi. The decision follows Vietnam's request for assistance 
made to the Japanese Government mission which visited Hanoi 
earlier this month to discuss details of a package of official 
loans. Tokyo plans to grant loans for multi-billion-dollar 
projects as one of [words indistinct] in developing countries to 
be financed by official credits in the next fiscal year, 
beginning next April. 
  The project of this new airport will be built south of the 
present airport, about 20 km north of Hanoi. This airport is 
expected to be completed around the year 2000. 

</TEXT>

