<F P=100> Vietnam </F>
<H3> <TI>   Decree on Marine Products Ministry </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Decree on Marine Products Ministry </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2706025294 Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network in Vietnamese 
1430 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2706025294 </F>
<F P=104>  Hanoi Voice of Vietnam Network </F>
<F P=105>  Vietnamese </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] On 21 June the government issued Decree No. 50/CT 
to regulate duties, authority, and organization of the Ministry 
of Marine Products. The decree consists of five articles. The 
first article says that the Ministry of Marine Products is 
authorized by the state to carry out state management function 
in marine products including rearing, catching, processing, 
protecting, and developing all marine product resources. 
  Article No. 2 determines concrete duties and authority of 
the 
ministry. 
  Article No. 3 determines the structure of the ministry 
consisting of the organizations that help the minister carry out 
state management role in the sector, and the professional 
organizations. 
  Article No. 5 stresses that the minister of marine products, 
other ministers and deputy ministers from ministries and other 
ministerial level agencies, heads of government agencies, 
chairmen of people's committees of provinces and cities are 
responsible for implementing this decree. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

