<H3> <TI>   Evans Comments on Jakarta Publications Ban </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Evans Comments on Jakarta Publications Ban </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2606131094 Melbourne Radio Australia in English 1100 GMT 
26 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2606131094 </F>
<F P=104>  Melbourne Radio Australia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Australia's foreign minister, Gareth Evans, says 
the recent crackdown on press freedom in Indonesia has not 
signalled a move away from liberalization by Jakarta. Senator 
Evans says he believes Prime Minister Paul Keating will raise 
the banning of three Indonesian news magazines with President 
Suharto during his visit to indonesia. Mr. Keating leaves for 
Jakarta tomorrow. 
  Speaking on commercial television, Senator Evans said that 
Indonesian society was undergoing profound change and setbacks 
were unavoidable. 
  [Begin Evans recording] This is part and parcel of the 
bumps, and grinds and advances and retreats that are associated 
with a major society in the process of major transition. I 
think the underlying movement is clear and upward and onward and 
all those fronts but there is bound, I fear, to be some retreat 
along the way. [end recording] 

</TEXT>

