<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Pyongyang, Seoul Agree To Top-Level Talks </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Pyongyang, Seoul Agree To Top-Level Talks </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Radio Notes Agreement for N-S Summit </H4>

<F P=102> SK2806132394 Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1238 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> SK2806132394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang Korean Central Broadcasting Network 
in Korean 1238 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Korean </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A deputy premier-level preliminary contact to hold 
North-South top-level talks [choegowigup hoedam] took place in 
Panmunjom on 28 June 1994. At the contact, the two sides agreed 
on the following points: 
  The two sides will hold North-South top-level talks in 
Pyongyang from 25 to 27 July 1994. 
  The itinerary of the stay can be extended further if 
necessary. 
  The next talks will be decided on at the will of the two 
sides' top-level officials [choegowigubui ttusettara]. 
  The composition and scale of the delegation to North-South 
top- level talks, formats of talks, an itinerary, dispatch of 
advance teams, procedures of visits, guarantee of conveniences, 
guarantee of personal safety, and other procedural matters will 
be discussed and agreed at a delegates contact attended by, from 
each side, one delegate to the preliminary contact and two 
accompanying officials. 
  A delegates contact will be held at Tongilgak, on the North 
side's area of Panmunjom, at 1000 on 1 July, Friday, 1994. 
  The two sides will make joint efforts to built atmospheres 
of 
North-South top-level talks favorable to reconciliation, unity, 
trust, and understanding. 
  28 June 1994 
  [Signed] Kim Yong-sun, chairman of the Reunification Policy 
Committee of the DPRK Supreme People's Assembly and head of the 
North side's delegation to a vice premier-level preliminary 
contact for North-South top-level talks 
  Yi Hong-ku, ROK [taehan minguk] deputy prime minister and 
minister of the National Unification Board and senior delegate 
of the South side to a vice premier-level preliminary contact 
for South-North top-level talks 

</TEXT>

