<H3> <TI>   KCNA Notes Start of Seoul Subway Workers' Strike </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    KCNA Notes Start of Seoul Subway Workers' Strike </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2506050394 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0442 GMT 25 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2506050394 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 25 (KCNA) -- The Seoul Subway 
Workers Union entered a general strike at 4 on the morning of 
June 24, according to radio reports from Seoul. 
  Though the trade union had final negotiations with the 
company on their wages, the latter persistently refused to 
accept its demand. The unionists are now on a sit-in strike at 
Korea University, the Myongdong Cathedral in Seoul and two other 
places of the city. 
  The sympathy strike of subway workers in Seoul and Pusan in 
the wake of the start of the general strike by locomotive 
engineers throughout South Korea will tie up the traffic at the 
worst, said the reports. 

</TEXT>

