  [Text] Pyongyang, June 26 (KCNA) -- The U.S. imperialists 
staged a provocative mid-air refuelling exercise against the 
North in the South Korean airspace day and night on June 23, 
military sources said. 
  The exercise involved two overseas-based refuelling tankers 
and scores of fighter-bombers and assault planes of the U.S. 
Airforce in South Korea. 
  The reckless play with fire was aimed at increasing the 
anti-North long-distance surprise attack capacity of the fighter 
planes of the U.S. Seventh Airforce. 
  The U.S. imperialists deployed Japan-based pursuit-assault 
planes and electronic jamming planes in U.S. Airforce bases in 
South Korea on the same day. 

