<H3> <TI>   NODONG SINMUN Warns Against Japanese Militarism </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    NODONG SINMUN Warns Against Japanese Militarism </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2806050194 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0451 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2806050194 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Extreme Fervor for Reinvasion" -- KCNA headline] </F>
  [Text] Pyongyang, June 28 (KCNA) -- NODONG SINMUN today 
comments on the growing danger of Japanese militarism. 
  The news analyst says: 
  The Japanese reactionaries dispatch more and more soldiers 
of 
the "Self-Defence Forces" [SDF] overseas for military exercises. 
They unhesitatingly utter such words as denying the criminal 
nature of the past war of aggression and inciting militarism. 
They undisguisedly work to fascistize the domestic system and 
legitimate overseas military action. 
  Through the enactment of an "emergency law" and revision of 
the "law on the SDF" they try to legitimate the overseas 
dispatch and military action of the "SDF" and mobilize the 
manpower and material resources of Japan lock, stock and barrel 
for military reinvasion. 
  Facts show the Japanese militarists, taking advantage of the 
failure of the policy of strength of superpowers, are going to 
revive the old empire and repeat the history of aggression. 
  The reinvasion fervour of the revived militarist ghosts has 
reached the extremity. 
  The Japanese reactionaries' talk about "threat" and "crisis 
in security" is an excuse for justifying their militarist acts 
for aggression. Under this pretext, they are inciting the 
consciousness of crisis and war at home and building public 
opinion to malrevise the "peaceful Constitution" and the "law on 
the SDF" and enact a wartime law. 
  The danger of revived militarism of Japan today is 
incomparably greater than it was. 
  Their acts for military reinvasion, however, lead to the 
same 
doom of Japanese imperialism that ran riot in aggression on Asia 
in the past. 
  They must learn a lesson from the past defeat and act with 
discretion. 

</TEXT>

