<H3> <TI>   Meeting Protests `Suppression' of Chongnyon </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Meeting Protests `Suppression' of Chongnyon </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2806000694 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1501 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2806000694 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

<F P=106> ["Emergency Meeting Protesting Suppression of Chongnyon and </F>
Persecution of Koreans in Japan Held in Tokyo" -- KCNA headline] 
  [Text] Tokyo, June 25 [dateline as received] (KNS-KCNA) -- 
An emergency meeting protesting the suppression of the General 
Association of Korean Residents in Japan (Chongnyon) by the 
Japanese police and its persecution of Koreans in Japan was held 
in Tokyo on June 21. 
  Attending it were Toshio Nejima, secretary general of the 
National Liaison Council of Trade Unions, Hiroshi Wakabayashi, 
secretary general of the Japan Committee for Supporting the 
Independent and Peaceful Reunification of Korea, and other 
public figures and citizens, more than 200 in all. 
  Japanese lawyer Shigeru Tokoi at the meeting roundly exposed 
the illegality and injustice of the search of the Osaka and 
Kyoto prefectural organisations of Chongnyon by the Japanese 
police and denounced it as a political crackdown designed to 
collect information for the destruction of Chongnyon and enact 
"an emergency law". 
  An appeal was adopted at the meeting. 
  The appeal said that the Japanese Government must 
immediately 
express apology and repentance to Chongnyon and Koreans in 
Japan. "The governmnt's policy must not be sanctions against the 
DPRK but the establishment of Japan-DPRK diplomatic relations 
and postwar compensation," it said, strongly demanding an early 
apology by the Japanese Government. 

</TEXT>

