<F P=100> North Korea </F>
<H3> <TI>   Moscow Meeting Marks Month of Solidarity </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Moscow Meeting Marks Month of Solidarity </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2806052494 Pyongyang KCNA in English 0446 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2806052494 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Moscow, June 25 [dateline as received] (KCNA) -- A 
meeting for opening the month of international solidarity with 
the Korean people was held in Moscow on June 24 under the 
sponsorship of the Russian Association for Friendly and Cultural 
Cooperation With the Democratic People's Republic of Korea. 
  The meeting speeches was addressed by Vladimir Tolschikov, 
chairman of the Central Council of the Russian Association, and 
others. 
  The speakers said that the war on June 25, 1950 was ignited 
by the U.S. imperialists and the South Korean authorities and 
that the Korean people honorably defended the freedom and 
independence of the country in the three-year war under the wise 
guidance of the great leader President Kim Il-song. 
  Noting that Korea has become a country most civilized in the 
world and the Korean people have become a people most organized 
in the world, they stressed: 
  The imperialists should know that threat or pressure will 
have no effect on Korea. 
  The DPRK is confidently advancing along the road of 
socialism 
because it is guided by President Kim Il-song, hero of the 
present times, and the dear leader Comrade Kim Chong-il. 
  The meeting adopted a letter to President Kim Il-song. 

</TEXT>

