<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 28 (KCNA) -- A bulletin was 
published on June 20 by the Mozambican Committee for Friendship 
With the People of the Democratic People's Republic of Korea and 
the Maputo City Committee of the Mozambique Liberation Front 
Party in joint name on the occasion of the month of 
international solidarity with the Korean people. 
  Printed in it are articles headlined "U.S. imperialists, the 
provoker of the Korean war," "U.S. imperialists, sworn enemy of 
the Korean people," "U.S. imperialists, murderers," "U.S. 
imperialists, disturber of peace", "U.S. imperialism denounced" 
and other articles. 
  Under the title "U.S. imperialists, the provoker of the 
Korean war" the bulletin says the United States ignited the 
Korean war by instigating the South Korean puppets on the 
prearranged script. Whatever intrigues they may resort to, the 
U.S. imperialists can never conceal their true color as the 
provoker of the war, says the bulletin. 

