<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 25 (KCNA) -- An inaugural meeting of 
the Mozambican committee for functions of solidarity with the 
Korean people was held in Maputo on June 16 on the occasion of 
the month of international solidarity with the Korean people 
(June 25-July 27). 
  Manuel Jose Antonio, home minister and chairman of the 
Mozambican committee for friendship with the people of the DPRK, 
was elected chairman of the new-born committee. 
  At the meeting, the chairman said various functions would be 
organised to denounce the crimes of U.S. imperialism and support 
the Korean people's cause of national reunification during the 
month of international solidarity with the Korean people. 
  He vowed to take the lead in the efforts to support the 
Korean people's cause of socialism and actively contribute to 
invariably developing friendly relations with the Korean people. 

