<H3> <TI>   Solidarity Meeting Held 18 Jun in Nepal </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Solidarity Meeting Held 18 Jun in Nepal </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   SK2806000794 Pyongyang KCNA in English 1508 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2806000794 </F>
<F P=104>  Pyongyang KCNA </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Pyongyang, June 27 (KCNA) -- A solidarity meeting 
supporting the just cause of the Korean people was held in 
Kathmandu on June 18. 
  Chairman of the Nepal Workers and Peasants Party Narayan Man 
Bijukchhe declared at the meeting: "We will extend invariable 
support to the government and the people of the Democratic 
People's Republic of Korea in all their efforts for the peace 
and security of the Korean peninsula and its denuclearisation." 
Manik Lal Shrestha, chairman of the Nepal-Korea Friendship 
Association, noted that the "resolution" adopted at the board of 
governors of the International Atomic Energy Agency [IAEA] is a 
prelude to the "sanctions" of the United Nations against the 
DPRK and virtually a declaration of war. He fully supported the 
Korean people who gave a decisive answer to the unjustifiable 
"step" of the IAEA. Member of parliament Shibash Nembag, said: 
"It is our duty, morality and conscience to extend militant 
support and solidarity to the fraternal Korean people. The 
Korean people and the world's peaceloving people will surely 
frustrate the moves of the imperialists and defend their just 
cause". 
  A letter to the great leader President Kim Il-song was 
adopted at the meeting. 

</TEXT>

