<F P=100> Brunei, Malaysia &amp; Singapore </F>
<F P=101> Malaysia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Minister: U.S. Needs To Hear East Asian Views </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Minister: U.S. Needs To Hear East Asian Views </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2806084594 Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia in English 0600 
GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2806084594 </F>
<F P=104>  Kuala Lumpur Voice of Malaysia </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Foreign Minister Datuk Abdullah Ahmad Badawi said 
the United States should not have made negative statements on 
the proposed East Asia Economic Caucus [EAEC] until the East 
Asian nations had given their views. He said the United States 
should first listen to the views of the East Asian nations. 
  He said ASEAN will hold a meeting in East Asian countries 
soon to discuss the matter officially. He added that when all 
the East Asian countries have stated their views, then the other 
countries can give their comments. He said this after receiving 
the Russian Minister of Culture Yevgeniy Sidorov and the 
Secretary General of Libyan People's Congress on Foreign Affairs 
(Chad Mujabba) at his ministry in Kuala Lumpur. 
  He said for the first time, the East Asian countries should 
discuss the matter first as the issue affects them. Datuk 
Abdullah was asked about the government's efforts to make the 
EAEC a reality after the U.S. has opposed the proposal. 

</TEXT>

