<F P=100> Mongolia </F>
<H3> <TI>   UNDP To Fund Management Development Program </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    UNDP To Fund Management Development Program </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2406082294 Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME in English 1625 GMT 23 Jun 
94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2406082294 </F>
<F P=104>  Ulaanbaatar MONTSAME </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Ulaanbaatar, June 23 (OANA-MONTSAME) -- Permanent 
representative of the United Nations Development Program to 
Mongolia Jan. V. Switering and the chairman of the National 
Development Department of Mongolia Ch. Ulaan signed today the 
projects concept on development of management and management 
system, reforming the state governing and state service, to a 
value of 2.7 million U.S. dollars. With signing of these 
documents realization of the government programme of development 
of management meant for 5 years and directed to reforming the 
state governing and management will start in cooperation with 
the UNO, donor countries, international organizations. Four 
other projects of the given programme on decentralization and 
consolidation of local administrations, development of the 
private sector of economy, structural reconstruction of 
privatized enterprises, strengthening of the system of training 
of officials are also planned to be realized with technical 
assistance of Sweden, Japan, Denmark, Holland, Germany, 
Australia and other countries in the course of the coming five 
years. 

</TEXT>

