<H4>    Aides Appointed to Delegation </H4>

<F P=102> SK2806015594 Seoul YONHAP in English 0148 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2806015594 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Seoul, June 28 (YONHAP) -- The government has 
appointed four bureau director-general-level officials as aides 
to the three-member delegation to the inter-Korean preliminary 
contact, it was learned Tuesday. 
  The four are Ku Pon-tae, chief policy-maker of the 
unification board; Chang Chae-yong, chief of the American 
affairs bureau of the Foreign Ministry; Om Ik-chun, assistant to 
the prime minister; and Yi Chae-ho, a member of the Inter-Korean 
Dialogue Secretariat. 
  They will assist chief delegate Yi Hong-ku (deputy premier 
and unification minister) and delegates Chong Chong-uk (senior 
presidential secretary for foreign affairs and national 
security) and Yun Yo-chun (special assistant to the prime 
minister) during the preliminary meeting which opened at the 
truce village of Panmunjom Tuesday morning. 
  A government official said the decision had been made Sunday 
to select the aides from among bureau director-general-level 
officials. 

</TEXT>

