<H4>    South Proposes 25 Jul Summit </H4>

<F P=102> SK2806043394 Seoul YONHAP in English 0427 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2806043394 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Panmunjom, June 28 (YONHAP) -- Seoul proposed 
exchange visits between South and North Korean capitals in 
arranging inter-Korean summit sometime mid-July at preparatory 
contact Tuesday, informed sources said. 
  South Korean Deputy Premier Yi Hong-ku, chief representative 
for the Seoul side, proposed that the leaders of the two Koreas 
exchange visits between Seoul and Pyongyang for mutuality. 
  Seoul reportedly suggested July 25-26 for the summit date 
and 
showed flexibility on which city should host first as long as 
the summit is arranged next month. 
  North Korea's top delegate Kim Yong-sun is said to have 
proposed an August meeting in Pyongyang. 

</TEXT>

