<H3> <TI>   Reports on 28 Jun North-South Contact Continue </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reports on 28 Jun North-South Contact Continue </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    2d Summit Details Not Decided </H4>

<F P=102> SK2806091294 Seoul YONHAP in English 0906 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> SK2806091294 </F>
<F P=104>  Seoul YONHAP </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Panmunjom, June 28 (YONHAP) -- Inter-Korean summit 
will open for the first time in over four decades July 25-27 in 
the North Korean capital of Pyongyang. 
  The historic agreement came after hours of working-level 
negotiations at the truce village of Panmunjom. 
  Talks to settle protocol details will open in the Northern 
side of the border on July 1. 
  Date and site of the second summit will be decided at next 
month's first summit. 

</TEXT>

