<H3> <TI>   Reports on Issues Related to Deregulation </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Reports on Issues Related to Deregulation </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    Keidanren Chief Welcomes Move </H4>

<F P=102> OW2806034194 Tokyo KYODO in English 0322 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2806034194 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 28 KYODO -- The chairman of Keidanren, 
the Federation of Economic Organizations, welcomed Tuesday [28 
June] a deregulation package released by the government the same 
day. 
  Shoichiro Toyoda released a statement saying the contents of 
the plan compiled by the administrative reform promotion 
headquarters warrants acceptance both domestically and abroad. 
  But he said the important thing is to put the plan into 
practice, calling for the government to take necessary measures 
as soon as possible, such as modification of the law. 
  Toyoda also suggested establishing an independent 
organization to monitor the progress of deregulation. 
  The government plan contains 279 deregulatory items under 
real estate, financial services, information and 
telecommunications areas. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

