<H3> <TI>   Political Situation Report From Tokyo Continues </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Political Situation Report From Tokyo Continues </PHRASE></F></HT>
<H4>    SDPJ Wants To Talk With Coalition </H4>

<F P=102> OW2806043294 Tokyo KYODO in English 0407 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2806043294 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 28 KYODO -- The Social Democratic Party 
(SDP) [Social Democratic Party of Japan -- SDPJ] wants to 
discuss forming a new government with the ruling coalition, the 
key strategist of the coalition said Tuesday [28 June]. 
  Ichiro Ozawa, secretary general of Shinseito, a key party in 
the coalition, told reporters the coalition has accepted the 
SDP's offer to meet. 
  The SDP, which is the second largest opposition party, faces 
a crucial choice of whether it would return to the coalition or 
forge an alliance with the boggest opposition Liberal Democratic 
Party (LDP), SDP's archrival so far. The LDP was ousted from 
government last August after 38 years in power. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

