<H3> <TI>   Hata Welcomes Agreement on Korean Summit </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Hata Welcomes Agreement on Korean Summit </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2806132994 Tokyo KYODO in English 1314 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2806132994 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 28 KYODO -- Prime Minister Tsutomu Hata 
on Tuesday welcomed the agreement between North and South Korea 
to hold their first summit meeting next month, saying it is 
"good news." 
  North and South Korean officials agreed earlier in the day 
to 
hold a meeting of their leaders in Pyongyang on July 25-27, 
followed by a second meeting at a later date, with the place 
still to be decided. 
  The summit would also have a good effect on the relations 
between Japan and North Korea, Hata told reporters. 
  On the prospects for Japanese economic and technological 
assistance to North Korea, Hata predicted smooth progress if the 
nuclear issue is settled in forthcoming high-level talks between 
the United States and North Korea. 

</TEXT>

