<H3> <TI>   Yen's Appreciation Viewed as `Detrimental' </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Yen's Appreciation Viewed as `Detrimental' </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   OW2706072694 Tokyo KYODO in English 0714 GMT 27 Jun 94 </F>
<F P=103> OW2706072694 </F>
<F P=104>  Tokyo KYODO </F>
<F P=105>  English </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] Tokyo, June 27 KYODO -- Vice Trade Minister Hideaki 
Kumano called Monday [27 June] for joint action by 
industrialized nations to stem the yen's rise against the 
dollar, calling the strong yen abnormal and detrimental to the 
global economy. 
  Kumano told a news conference the yen's sharp appreciation 
against the U.S. dollar does not reflect the fundamental factors 
of the Japanese economy and the government is concerned about it. 
  The yen closed at a postwar high of 99.93 yen against the 
dollar in Tokyo on Monday. 
  Kumano disagreed that the dollar's weakness against the 
German mark and other European currencies reflects the loss of 
confidence in the U.S. economy and added the dollar's decline is 
not desirable for the U.S. economy. 

</TEXT>

