  [Text] Australian Prime Minister Paul Keating flew into 
Jakarta yesterday afternoon for a three-day working visit to 
Indonesia. Foreign Minister ad interim Susilo Sudarman was on 
hand at the Halim Perdanakusumah International Airport to 
welcome Australian Prime Minister Paul Keating and his 26-member 
delegation. 
  According to the schedule, Paul Keating will make a courtesy 
call on President Suharto at Merdeka Palace today and among 
other things, will discuss the preparations for the upcoming 
APEC summit to be held in November 1994. The Australian prime 
minister will also officially open the Australian trade 
exhibition, Australia Today 1994, tomorrow in Jakarta. 

