<F P=100> Cambodia </F>
<H3> <TI>   Chea Sim Supports Bill To Outlaw Khmer Rouge </TI></H3>
<HT><F P=107><PHRASE>    Chea Sim Supports Bill To Outlaw Khmer Rouge </PHRASE></F></HT>

<F P=102>   BK2806142794 Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0500 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=103> BK2806142794 </F>
<F P=104>  Phnom Penh National Radio of Cambodia Network 
in Cambodian 0500 GMT 28 Jun 94 </F>

<F P=105> Cambodian </F>


<TEXT>
BFN 

  [Text] A bill to outlaw the Party of Democratic Kampuchea 
[PDK] will be presented to the National Assembly for approval in 
early July. National Assembly Chairman Samdech Chea Sim says he 
hopes all members of the National Assembly of the Kingdom of 
Cambodia will support this bill to place the PDK outside of the 
Royal Government's laws. Approval or disapproval of the bill 
requires a two-thirds vote. 
  The Royal Government had considered presenting this bill to 
the National Assembly for a decision (?at its special session) 
but postponed it because His Majesty Norodom Sihanouk Varaman, 
king of the Kingdom of Cambodia, wanted to pursue the peace 
negotiations. 

</TEXT>

</DOC>

